  "body": "Sorry if I've missed something here but from my understanding, the process for creating a `SyncAggregate` for a block at slot `x` is to collect the best `SyncCommitteeContribution` from slot `x - 1` and aggregate them as per `process_sync_committee_contributions` from https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/dev/specs/altair/validator.md#block-proposal.\r\n\r\nThen during block processing, `process_sync_committee` uses `state.current_sync_committee` where `state` has already had slots processed up to and including `x`.\r\n\r\nGiven that, the aggregate indices in the `SyncAggregate` will refer to the sync committee at slot `x - 1` but if `x` is the first slot of a new sync committee period, `state.current_sync_committee` will have already been updated and now point to the new sync committee.  The wrong validator public keys will then be collected in `participant_pubkeys` and signature validation will fail.",
