    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Because we get rid of `previous_sync_committee` in state but always know `current` and `next`, the job for the `next` needs to begin 1 slot prior to the start of the period so that they can be included at the 0th slot of the period.\r\n\r\nThat is, the `current_sync_committee` votes on blocks from slots ranging `[period_start_slot - 1, period_end_slot)` and is included in blocks with slots ranging  `[period_start_slot, period_end_slot]`\r\n\r\nI'll clean up the language in the validator guide and make sure this is tested",
